# Environment Variables Reference

Copy this file to `.env` in both `frontend/` and `sanity/` directories and fill in your values.

## Frontend (.env)

```env
# Sanity Configuration
SANITY_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id_here
SANITY_DATASET=production
SANITY_API_VERSION=2024-01-01

# Optional: For authenticated requests (if needed)
SANITY_API_TOKEN=your_optional_token_here

# Optional: Enable real-time updates (set to false for CDN caching)
SANITY_USE_CDN=true
```

## Sanity (.env)

```env
# Sanity Project
SANITY_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id_here
SANITY_DATASET=production
SANITY_AUTH_TOKEN=your_auth_token_here
```

## Getting Your Values

### SANITY_PROJECT_ID
1. Go to [sanity.io/manage](https://sanity.io/manage)
2. Click on your project
3. Copy the Project ID from the settings

### SANITY_AUTH_TOKEN (Sanity only)
1. In [sanity.io/manage](https://sanity.io/manage)
2. Go to API tokens
3. Create a new token with "Editor" role
4. Copy the token value

### SANITY_API_VERSION
- Use current date in YYYY-MM-DD format
- Example: 2024-01-01

## Security Notes

- Never commit `.env` files with real tokens to GitHub
- Add `.env` to `.gitignore`
- Use GitHub Secrets for CI/CD deployments
- Keep API tokens private and rotate them regularly
